As mentioned above, we found that the size of these islands becomes smaller as the time delay $\tau$ is increased.  Fig.~\ref{fig:lorenz_k} shows the stability slices of the coupled system for fixed coupling strengths, and Fig.~\ref{fig:lorenz_tau} shows the stability slices of the coupled system for fixed delays. Corresponding to the results with the R\"{o}ssler system, for fixed coupling strength $\sigma$, the size and number of active stability regions in the $\tau$ - $\lambda$ space are found to depend (non-monotonically) on the value of the coupling strength as shown in Fig.~\ref{fig:lorenz_k}, and for fixed delay $\tau$, there is generally either none or a single connected stability region in the $\tau$ - $\lambda$ space as shown in Fig.~\ref{fig:lorenz_tau}. As with the R\"{o}ssler system figures, the regions with the slanted lines represent the active stability regions. 

